    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-06-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>,
                                    Secretary of State, to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-06-29">
                        <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 29,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p>The Secretary of State has the honor to lay before the President the
                                inclosed telegram of this date, just received from Mr. Pierrepont,
                                asking instructions as to steps to be taken in regard to Colonel
                                Ryan and his expeditionary party of four hundred men at New
                                    York.<note n="1" xml:id="d392fn1">For inclosure see preceding
                                    letter.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
